                <span></span>
            </div>
            <p>Thank you for your interest in the Horticulture Club's Plant Sale. This year it took place on April 8 and we thank everyone for coming out and supporting our club. This year has paved the way for future Plant Sales to be even bigger. Hope everyone is enjoying their new plants. If you have any questions you can check out the calendar below to stay updated on upcoming plant sales or email us at tamuhorticultureclub@gmail.com.
            </p>
            <br>
            <p>The Spring Plant Sale is the Horticulture Club's largest fundraiser of the year. Through the support of our community, members have the opportunity to learn about plants by hands on experience in preparation for this sale such as cultivating and maintaining the inventory. This fundraiser has a lasting impact on our club allowing us to be able to send members to represent Texas A&M in horticultural competitions across the country. 
            </p>
            <div class="plantsale-action">
